5:40 False News galore! The only official reason Starlink is banned in Russia is because they don't have a dedicated "russian regional" server on the russian ground. The law that states that any foreign operator should have their servers for data of russian citizens to be on russian territory is an old one and Facebook, YouTube and Google follow it without questions.
Also "Sfera" (Sphere) is not Starlink analogue, it's a government's satellite data network project. It's made by government for primary governmental reasons.
